Power BI DAX Measures
Total Sales
Total Sales = SUM('Sheet1'[No of Sales of Cards])
Unique Customers
Unique Customers = DISTINCTCOUNT('Sheet1'[Customer Name])
Average Rating
Average Rating = AVERAGE('Sheet1'[Rating])
Positive Marks
Positive Marks = SUM('Sheet1'[Positive Mark])
Negative Marks
Negative Marks = SUM('Sheet1'[Negative Mark])
Total Banks
Total Banks = DISTINCTCOUNT('Sheet1'[Bank Name])

